WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:08.000
[birds chirping]

00:11.280 --> 00:14.120
[rapid gunfire nearby]

00:14.160 --> 00:16.160
[indistinct shouting, screaming]

00:20.320 --> 00:22.280
[gunfire continues]

00:22.320 --> 00:24.320
[screaming]

00:30.520 --> 00:33.120
[indistinct shouting]

00:39.320 --> 00:41.320
[screaming, crying]

00:41.360 --> 00:43.160
Mama!

00:43.200 --> 00:44.840
[overlapping shouting]

00:44.880 --> 00:46.600
[sobbing]:
Adidja!

00:46.640 --> 00:48.280
Adidja!

00:48.320 --> 00:52.960
-[speaks foreign language]
-Mama! Mama!

00:53.000 --> 00:56.040
[soldier shouting
in foreign language]

00:56.080 --> 00:58.600
[screaming]

00:58.640 --> 01:00.400
[rapid gunfire]

01:00.440 --> 01:01.920
-Adidja!
-Mama!

01:01.960 --> 01:05.560
Adidja. Adidja.

01:05.600 --> 01:07.600
[shouting in foreign language]

01:12.040 --> 01:13.760
[screaming]

01:14.640 --> 01:18.560
Mama! Mama! Mama!

01:21.960 --> 01:24.480
Mama! Mama!

01:28.080 --> 01:30.080
[airplane engines whirring]

01:38.600 --> 01:40.200
Have you ever been
on a plane before?

01:58.480 --> 02:00.640
♪ ♪

02:15.480 --> 02:16.600
Joshua.

02:16.640 --> 02:18.480
I'll, um, leave you to lock up

02:18.520 --> 02:20.200
after you get your things,
if that's okay.

02:20.240 --> 02:23.320
I can't be in there anymore.

02:23.360 --> 02:25.720
No, of course. I'm sorry.

02:27.320 --> 02:29.560
She was a good person,
she didn't deserve this.

02:34.040 --> 02:36.040
[door closes]

02:36.080 --> 02:37.320
ADIDJA:
Who lives here?

02:37.360 --> 02:40.480
Uh, nobody anymore.

02:40.520 --> 02:43.440
But we'll be safe here.

02:45.440 --> 02:47.840
Nobody's safe.

02:51.600 --> 02:52.840
Are you hungry?

02:52.880 --> 02:55.720
Yeah? Come on.

03:00.080 --> 03:02.400
Help yourself.
Whatever you want.

03:09.560 --> 03:12.480
W-Would it be okay for a second?
I've just got to find something.

03:12.520 --> 03:14.160
Yeah?

03:22.800 --> 03:24.800
[sighs]

03:37.640 --> 03:39.640
[woman singing
in foreign language]

04:01.920 --> 04:03.920
♪ ♪

04:16.760 --> 04:21.160
MARTIN: Excuse me,
I'm looking for Mr. Kasongo.

04:21.200 --> 04:23.440
-That's him over there.
-Ah, thank you.

04:30.360 --> 04:32.760
-Monsieur Kasongo?
-Oui.

04:32.800 --> 04:36.840
Ah. May I?

04:36.880 --> 04:38.800
[grunts, sniffs]

04:38.840 --> 04:40.520
Do you speak English
by any chance?

04:40.560 --> 04:43.640
I-I do, but not as much
as I used to.

04:43.680 --> 04:45.640
Ah. [chuckles]

04:45.680 --> 04:47.680
Um, well,

04:47.720 --> 04:49.840
I'm doing a research project

04:49.880 --> 04:54.200
and talking to former officers
from the Air Force.

04:54.240 --> 04:57.200
Ah, it's been ten years
since I left.

04:57.240 --> 04:58.880
Ten?

04:58.920 --> 05:01.680
This is probably
a stupid question, but do...

05:01.720 --> 05:04.040
-Go on.
-Well...

05:04.080 --> 05:07.840
Do you remember
a-a high-ranking officer

05:07.880 --> 05:10.040
with a distinctive voice?

05:10.080 --> 05:12.560
Sharp. Grating. Rasping.

05:14.280 --> 05:18.040
No... Never mind.

05:18.080 --> 05:20.080
There is a man.

05:21.520 --> 05:24.800
Major General Azikiwe.

05:26.320 --> 05:28.920
Well known for his voice

05:28.960 --> 05:32.000
that is as sharp as his temper.

05:32.040 --> 05:34.640
Azikiwe. Uh-huh.

05:34.680 --> 05:36.760
Men could never forget.

05:36.800 --> 05:39.160
Really.

05:41.000 --> 05:42.520
Thank you.

05:42.560 --> 05:46.160
[churchgoers chatting
indistinctly]

05:46.200 --> 05:48.000
So wh-what happened?

05:48.040 --> 05:50.840
[chuckles] Well, I'm pretty sure

05:50.880 --> 05:53.320
that he is not our man.

05:53.360 --> 05:55.520
KASONGO [on recording]: I do,
but not as much as I used to.

05:55.560 --> 05:57.160
MARTIN:
Ah.

05:57.200 --> 05:59.360
Yeah, you're right,
that's not him.

05:59.400 --> 06:02.800
However, he did give me a name.

06:02.840 --> 06:06.960
Azikiwe. A major general.

06:07.000 --> 06:09.240
With a voice, apparently,
as distinctive

06:09.280 --> 06:11.560
as the one
that you say you remember.

06:11.600 --> 06:12.880
Okay.

06:12.920 --> 06:15.120
Don't forget this.

06:15.160 --> 06:19.040
The museum you borrowed it from
probably wants it back.

06:20.800 --> 06:23.440
[sighs] I never thought I'd say
this, but I'm glad to see you.

06:23.480 --> 06:26.360
MARTIN:
Yes, me, too.

06:26.400 --> 06:28.280
Georgia, this is Ariel.

06:28.320 --> 06:31.440
Hi. I've heard a great deal
about you.

06:31.480 --> 06:34.200
I haven't heard nearly enough
about you.

06:39.240 --> 06:41.840
This is Adidja.

06:41.880 --> 06:44.240
Um, Ariel, come in here and...

06:44.280 --> 06:47.360
um, no, mind your head.

06:47.400 --> 06:50.120
Just wait there a moment,
would you?

06:50.160 --> 06:51.640
Can we have a word?

06:51.680 --> 06:53.040
Yeah.

06:57.680 --> 06:59.560
Who's that?

06:59.600 --> 07:01.280
She was taken to be a soldier

07:01.320 --> 07:04.040
by one of the militia groups
in the east.

07:04.080 --> 07:05.600
And?

07:05.640 --> 07:07.760
And I saw her as I was driving
away from the mine,

07:07.800 --> 07:09.360
and I-I-I wasn't thinking,

07:09.400 --> 07:12.000
and I couldn't leave her there.

07:12.040 --> 07:14.520
You can't go around Hoovering up
all the child soldiers in Africa

07:14.560 --> 07:15.920
because you feel sorry for them.

07:15.960 --> 07:17.560
What are you gonna do next?
Cure poverty?

07:17.600 --> 07:19.600
Oh, my God, you really don't
think much of me, do you?

07:19.640 --> 07:20.880
Oh, Georgia, no...

07:20.920 --> 07:22.400
No, you had me blocked
from the army

07:22.440 --> 07:24.040
because you didn't think
I could handle it.

07:24.080 --> 07:25.840
And now here you are again,
fucking patronizing me.

07:25.880 --> 07:27.320
I did it for your own good.

07:27.360 --> 07:30.640
I promised your dad
that I'd look after you.

07:30.680 --> 07:32.800
And after Violet,
you just weren't ready.

07:32.840 --> 07:34.320
GEORGIA:
In your opinion.

07:34.360 --> 07:35.600
Hi.

07:35.640 --> 07:37.600
Have you slept?

07:37.640 --> 07:39.920
[sighs]
A bit. On the plane.

07:39.960 --> 07:41.400
I... I'm all right.

07:41.440 --> 07:43.960
I'm fine.

07:44.000 --> 07:46.640
Georgia, I'm sorry.
I don't mean to upset you.

07:46.680 --> 07:48.360
But I'm worried.

07:48.400 --> 07:50.920
I'm bloody worried about what's
happening to you.

07:50.960 --> 07:53.800
I know, I'm sorry.

07:53.840 --> 07:57.040
Look, I really do appreciate you
coming out here.

08:01.200 --> 08:02.760
I've looked
in all Judith's stuff,

08:02.800 --> 08:05.760
and there's nothing
about Pieter Bello.

08:05.800 --> 08:08.720
I can't work out where Will fits
into all this.

08:08.760 --> 08:10.760
Oh, I'm sorry.

08:10.800 --> 08:13.520
-I need to...
-Yeah, uh,
the bathroom's that way.

08:13.560 --> 08:17.680
Sorry, bloody malaria tablets
don't agree with me.

08:19.200 --> 08:22.080
[door opens]

08:22.120 --> 08:24.080
[door closes]

08:24.120 --> 08:25.520
What was it like?

08:28.560 --> 08:32.640
Um, it was, um...

08:32.680 --> 08:35.120
It's strange.

08:35.160 --> 08:38.760
Until it happened, I felt like
I'd been sleepwalking.

08:38.800 --> 08:42.400
Or running away from my old life
and that was all.

08:42.440 --> 08:46.880
Then, when the bomb went off
on that plane...

08:49.320 --> 08:52.200
...it felt like I woke up.

08:52.240 --> 08:54.560
And I knew I wanted to live.

08:54.600 --> 08:57.880
I just, I just knew.

08:57.920 --> 08:59.120
It's human nature, I suppose.

08:59.160 --> 09:00.760
GEORGIA:
Yeah.

09:00.800 --> 09:02.440
You were lucky.

09:02.480 --> 09:03.760
ARIEL:
Perhaps.

09:03.800 --> 09:05.760
That man...

09:05.800 --> 09:07.680
You're looking for this man?

09:07.720 --> 09:11.640
GEORGIA:
Yeah. Why?

09:11.680 --> 09:13.640
[Sadiki groaning]

09:13.680 --> 09:17.520
[groaning, whimpering]

09:23.280 --> 09:24.480
That looks bad.

09:24.520 --> 09:26.560
You should have someone look
at it.

09:26.600 --> 09:28.120
I'm not weak.

09:28.160 --> 09:29.240
I'll be fine.

09:30.200 --> 09:32.160
[Sadiki whimpers]

09:32.200 --> 09:35.760
♪ ♪

09:42.480 --> 09:46.080
[man singing
in foreign language]

10:05.600 --> 10:07.880
PIETER: I'll show you myself,
I'll show you the dead bodies.

10:10.200 --> 10:11.960
What are you doing in here?

10:13.360 --> 10:14.320
Hi.

10:14.360 --> 10:16.480
My friend is hurt.

10:16.520 --> 10:19.400
Could you help him?

10:19.440 --> 10:22.560
I'm in the middle
of something, yeah.

10:22.600 --> 10:25.240
Bladdy kadogos.

10:25.280 --> 10:27.200
Sorry about the interruption.

10:27.240 --> 10:28.800
Now, where were we, my friend?

10:28.840 --> 10:30.600
ADIDJA:
I saw him on the screen.

10:30.640 --> 10:32.760
I know where he is.

10:36.160 --> 10:37.800
MARTIN:
You sure it's here?

10:37.840 --> 10:40.360
This is where the man
in the photograph is? Yes?

10:40.400 --> 10:43.200
He said the name when he was
speaking with Mr. Bello.

10:43.240 --> 10:44.680
And he said the name
of the village.

10:44.720 --> 10:46.560
Masi-Kilembe, I remember.

10:46.600 --> 10:48.960
I could take Judith's other car.

10:49.000 --> 10:50.680
There's a 4x4 in the garage.

10:50.720 --> 10:52.920
MARTIN: Oh, come on.
This is a 15-hour journey

10:52.960 --> 10:54.640
through God-knows-where.

10:54.680 --> 10:56.640
GEORGIA: Yeah, but it will still
get me there quicker.

10:56.680 --> 10:58.760
Did he say anything else?
When you saw him?

10:58.800 --> 11:01.560
Only the place.

11:01.600 --> 11:03.600
[sighs] And how did he seem?

11:03.640 --> 11:05.360
W-Was he okay?
Was he well?

11:05.400 --> 11:07.720
He was shouting.

11:07.760 --> 11:09.880
Hmm.

11:09.920 --> 11:14.440
Go. We'll stay here and
track down General Azikiwe.

11:22.480 --> 11:24.480
♪ ♪

11:29.320 --> 11:31.320
[engine starts]

11:34.000 --> 11:36.080
All right, let's go.

12:04.640 --> 12:06.600
ARIEL:
Are we there yet?

12:06.640 --> 12:08.400
Yes, I think so.
[clears throat]

12:08.440 --> 12:11.840
Just give me a minute, and
I'll start this thing, and...

12:11.880 --> 12:14.120
Right.

12:14.160 --> 12:15.920
Your Dictaphone?

12:15.960 --> 12:18.080
-Yes, my Dictaphone.
-[laughs]

12:19.680 --> 12:21.560
I'll be back shortly.

12:21.600 --> 12:23.560
Yeah.

12:23.600 --> 12:25.840
[insects chirring]

12:40.200 --> 12:42.200
I've come to see your commander.

12:44.000 --> 12:46.760
[two beeps]

12:46.800 --> 12:48.240
AZIKIWE [over intercom]:
Oui?

12:48.280 --> 12:50.720
Am I speaking
to Major General Azikiwe?

12:50.760 --> 12:51.960
Yes. What do you want?

12:52.000 --> 12:54.080
My name is Alexander Ramsay.

12:54.120 --> 12:56.960
Um, I'm sorry to turn up
unannounced, as it were,

12:57.000 --> 13:00.160
but I'm doing some research,
and I would really appreciate it

13:00.200 --> 13:02.880
if I could have just
a few minutes of your time.

13:02.920 --> 13:06.840
Research? What kind of research
are you doing?

13:06.880 --> 13:08.680
It's for a book. I'm...

13:08.720 --> 13:11.760
I'm writing a... a history
of aviation in the Congo.

13:11.800 --> 13:14.000
[clears throat]

13:17.120 --> 13:19.120
Thank you.

13:41.480 --> 13:43.480
Out of my way.

13:48.400 --> 13:51.600
So... a history book, you say?

13:51.640 --> 13:54.960
Yes, indeed.
Precisely, yes.

13:55.000 --> 13:56.600
History is easy.

13:56.640 --> 13:58.480
It's what's in the past.

13:58.520 --> 14:00.840
This is true, yes.

14:00.880 --> 14:04.120
Ah! [laughs]

14:04.160 --> 14:06.960
-Rolls-Royce engine.
-Mm.

14:07.000 --> 14:09.080
-Musical.
-Mm.

14:09.120 --> 14:11.120
-[laughs]
-My favorite.

14:11.160 --> 14:13.200
Oh, thank you.
Thank you.

14:18.080 --> 14:20.080
[Martin clears throat]

14:20.120 --> 14:23.240
Yes, history, I think,
is, um-- is-is...

14:23.280 --> 14:26.480
is something that we can, um,
hopefully all learn from.

14:26.520 --> 14:28.880
-Don't you think?
-Perhaps.

14:28.920 --> 14:31.160
-[clears throat]
-Although sometimes

14:31.200 --> 14:33.840
I think nobody learns a thing
in this life.

14:33.880 --> 14:37.120
We just go around in circles.

14:37.160 --> 14:39.480
-[sniffles]
-May I offer you a drink?

14:39.520 --> 14:42.520
No, thank you.
Thank you, sir.

14:42.560 --> 14:45.960
So tell me...
what do you wish to know?

14:46.000 --> 14:50.800
As I said, I'm-I'm, uh...
writing a-a... a book,

14:50.840 --> 14:54.440
a history, uh, basically,
of, um, aviation in the Congo.

14:54.480 --> 14:56.120
Mm.

14:56.160 --> 14:59.600
And there is a chapter
specifically

14:59.640 --> 15:02.360
about, uh, Sankuru Airways.

15:02.400 --> 15:05.920
As you're aware, there-there was
a systematic failure

15:05.960 --> 15:07.440
of aviation...

15:07.480 --> 15:09.680
I do not understand
what you want of me.

15:09.720 --> 15:14.200
Well, um, the Air Force run
all the radar

15:14.240 --> 15:16.600
for Congolese aviation.

15:16.640 --> 15:19.800
And your unit assisted
the government.

15:19.840 --> 15:22.440
So I presume that
you-you would have been a party

15:22.480 --> 15:24.840
to the investigation...
[clears throat]

15:24.880 --> 15:29.200
after Sankuru Flight 19
went down.

15:31.920 --> 15:33.560
[clears throat]
I-I'm-I'm just trying

15:33.600 --> 15:37.680
to understand the accident
in the context of the whole...

15:47.760 --> 15:50.240
You can leave now.

15:52.320 --> 15:55.520
[clears throat] Yes, sir.
Well, thank you for your time.

15:55.560 --> 15:57.640
Um...

15:57.680 --> 15:59.680
[clears throat]

16:05.200 --> 16:07.360
[door closes]

16:12.720 --> 16:14.960
That man saw me at the airport.

16:15.000 --> 16:16.640
Sidney!

16:16.680 --> 16:18.800
Oui?

16:19.800 --> 16:21.800
[birds squawking]

16:26.480 --> 16:28.960
Jesus Christ.
What are you doing out here?

16:29.000 --> 16:31.160
Ariel, get back
in the vehicle now.

16:31.200 --> 16:34.120
Oh... it was very hot.

16:34.160 --> 16:36.800
[Ariel groans softly]

16:36.840 --> 16:38.840
Jesus, Martin.

16:38.880 --> 16:40.880
What's going on? Relax.

16:42.040 --> 16:44.880
-Was it him?
-[sighs]

16:44.920 --> 16:46.840
Martin, was it him?

16:46.880 --> 16:48.720
-[rewinding]
-Wait. Listen.

16:48.760 --> 16:50.720
AZIKIWE: Perhaps.
Although sometimes I think

16:50.760 --> 16:52.360
nobody learns a thing
in this life.

16:52.400 --> 16:53.880
-Oh, my God.
-Yeah?

16:53.920 --> 16:55.920
That's him. That's him!

17:02.280 --> 17:03.520
Follow them.

17:16.840 --> 17:19.120
You remind me of my dog.

17:19.160 --> 17:21.080
What?

17:21.120 --> 17:24.560
No. Sorry, I mean, he used
to stick his head out the window

17:24.600 --> 17:26.120
in the back of the car.

17:26.160 --> 17:28.760
We got him after my mom died.

17:28.800 --> 17:30.440
Lose a mom, get a dog.

17:30.480 --> 17:33.160
Suppose that's dad thinking
for you.

17:34.320 --> 17:36.280
His name was Peanut.

17:36.320 --> 17:38.400
The dog, not my dad.

17:38.440 --> 17:39.680
[Georgia laughs]

17:39.720 --> 17:43.240
Why did he stick his head
out the window?

17:43.280 --> 17:46.120
I think, just like you,
I think it just felt nice.

17:46.160 --> 17:48.240
Think it made him feel happy.

17:48.280 --> 17:50.840
He'd also stick
his whole tongue out,

17:50.880 --> 17:53.680
just sit there with it flapping
in the wind. [laughs]

18:01.120 --> 18:03.800
[both laugh]

18:07.840 --> 18:09.840
My mouth is dry.

18:09.880 --> 18:11.880
That it is. Here.

18:15.880 --> 18:17.840
ARIEL:
I need

18:17.880 --> 18:20.800
to meet Azikiwe in public.
I'll confront him.

18:20.840 --> 18:22.840
-Ariel.
-I'll pretend
I'm blackmailing him,

18:22.880 --> 18:25.720
and I'll-I'll get him on tape,
admitting to what he did.

18:25.760 --> 18:28.120
Look, as far as I'm concerned,

18:28.160 --> 18:31.760
that bastard Azikiwe
can rot in jail, but I am not

18:31.800 --> 18:33.360
going to put you at risk.

18:33.400 --> 18:35.000
I'm-I'm asking for your help.

18:35.040 --> 18:37.240
-I don't care about the risk.
-I do.

18:37.280 --> 18:39.400
Look, you promised.

18:39.440 --> 18:41.080
Well, I lied.

18:41.120 --> 18:43.560
I just wanted
to keep an eye on you,

18:43.600 --> 18:46.000
stop you doing anything stupid.

18:46.040 --> 18:48.560
I'm not gonna let a blind man
get himself killed.

18:48.600 --> 18:50.080
[sniffles]

18:50.120 --> 18:52.640
No matter what journey...

18:52.680 --> 18:55.640
[thud]

18:55.680 --> 18:57.680
Mar-Martin?

18:58.880 --> 19:00.880
Martin?

19:02.600 --> 19:04.520
Martin?

19:04.560 --> 19:06.560
[Martin groaning]

19:08.040 --> 19:10.600
Martin? Martin?

19:10.640 --> 19:13.160
Are-are you okay?

19:13.200 --> 19:15.200
What happened?

19:16.200 --> 19:18.480
It sounded like you passed out.

19:18.520 --> 19:23.040
Well, that would explain
what I'm doing on the floor.

19:23.080 --> 19:25.600
You should see a doctor.

19:25.640 --> 19:28.040
[sighs]
Listen.

19:28.080 --> 19:30.600
[sighs] Listen, I'll-I'll...
I'll be fine.

19:30.640 --> 19:32.400
-Don't be ridiculous.
-[groaning]: Oh.

19:32.440 --> 19:34.600
If you aren't well,
you can't help me,

19:34.640 --> 19:36.120
you can't help your friend.

19:36.160 --> 19:38.640
So, would you please go
to the hospital right now?

19:38.680 --> 19:40.960
All right. All right.

19:42.120 --> 19:43.800
[groans softly]

19:43.840 --> 19:45.360
Thank you.

19:45.400 --> 19:47.600
[Martin groans softly]

19:47.640 --> 19:50.640
I'll try not to be too long.

19:50.680 --> 19:52.640
Don't worry about me.

19:52.680 --> 19:54.760
-I'll be fine.
-Ah.

19:57.200 --> 19:59.200
Be careful.

20:01.480 --> 20:04.000
[indistinct chatter,
piano playing]

20:04.040 --> 20:06.320
Excuse me.

20:06.360 --> 20:09.000
Excuse me!

20:09.040 --> 20:10.640
Where's the nearest hospital?

20:10.680 --> 20:13.320
Rue Gamber.

20:13.360 --> 20:16.960
Not too far from here,
so it should be fine.

20:17.000 --> 20:18.960
There you go.

20:19.000 --> 20:21.040
-Thank you.
-Pleasure.

20:25.920 --> 20:28.320
[bell dings]

20:31.520 --> 20:33.800
[stuttering]:
Good book?

20:36.280 --> 20:38.160
[man speaking Icelandic
on audiobook]

20:38.200 --> 20:39.320
[phone buzzing]

20:39.360 --> 20:41.560
MALE AUTOMATED VOICE:
Beatrix hringir.

20:41.600 --> 20:44.000
-Beatrix hringir.
-[phone buzzing]

20:44.040 --> 20:47.320
Beatrix hringir.

20:47.360 --> 20:49.480
Beatrix?

20:49.520 --> 20:53.880
I just wanted to call to tell
you that I had the operation.

20:53.920 --> 20:56.160
-I thought you should know.
-And?

20:56.200 --> 20:58.320
I won't know for a while.

21:00.960 --> 21:03.920
I'm in Kinshasa.
I came.

21:03.960 --> 21:06.360
I'm glad. I'm-I'm...

21:06.400 --> 21:08.400
I didn't like the way

21:08.440 --> 21:10.040
we left things. I...

21:10.080 --> 21:12.000
I'm finally trying
to do a good thing.

21:12.040 --> 21:13.920
You're not a bad person, Ariel.

21:13.960 --> 21:15.600
I thought perhaps
you were calling me

21:15.640 --> 21:17.360
because of the package
I sent you.

21:17.400 --> 21:19.160
No. Nothing's arrived.

21:19.200 --> 21:22.360
It's-it's nothing much.

21:22.400 --> 21:24.920
I just knew
your surgery was coming up...

21:24.960 --> 21:26.440
[door opens]

21:26.480 --> 21:29.200
-Oh, uh, Beatrix?
-[door closes]

21:29.240 --> 21:32.040
Do you mind if I call you back
in a little bit?

21:32.080 --> 21:33.640
-Okay.
-Thank you.

21:33.680 --> 21:35.800
-Speak later.
-Martin?

21:35.840 --> 21:38.360
That was fast.

21:38.400 --> 21:40.800
What did they say?

21:42.640 --> 21:45.080
Martin?

21:47.040 --> 21:49.080
Is that you, Martin?

21:52.000 --> 21:54.000
Martin?

21:57.920 --> 21:59.720
-[groans]
-[yells]

21:59.760 --> 22:01.240
Don't move!

22:01.280 --> 22:03.080
[Ariel groans, pants]

22:03.120 --> 22:04.640
Don't fucking move.

22:04.680 --> 22:06.360
[panting]

22:06.400 --> 22:08.760
Stay still.

22:08.800 --> 22:11.400
[Ariel groans, Sidney sighs]

22:12.920 --> 22:15.160
[gasping]

22:15.200 --> 22:17.520
Be smart, okay?

22:17.560 --> 22:19.240
-Okay?
-Okay.

22:19.280 --> 22:21.440
Okay.

22:21.480 --> 22:23.360
-[quietly]: Okay.
-Be smart.

22:23.400 --> 22:26.640
-Yeah, I'll be...
-[plastic crunching]

22:26.680 --> 22:28.040
I'll be...

22:28.080 --> 22:30.600
I'll be smart.

22:38.800 --> 22:40.880
Where is your friend?

22:42.480 --> 22:46.200
He's-he's... he's gone.
He's gone home.

22:46.240 --> 22:48.640
He left a blind man alone?

22:48.680 --> 22:51.680
Yeah, I asked him to go.
His part was done.

22:51.720 --> 22:54.480
It doesn't matter.

22:54.520 --> 22:57.440
You are-are the one

22:57.480 --> 22:59.280
he recognized.

22:59.320 --> 23:01.480
You work for the general.

23:05.080 --> 23:07.320
Where does this end?

23:09.000 --> 23:13.000
Being a lapdog to a man who
murdered a plane full of people.

23:13.040 --> 23:15.400
Dealing with the shit

23:15.440 --> 23:18.040
so he can keep his hands clean.

23:18.080 --> 23:20.000
I'm no one's dog.

23:20.040 --> 23:22.040
Sure, you're a dog.

23:22.080 --> 23:24.760
You're a coward.

23:24.800 --> 23:26.600
You're here to murder
a blind man

23:26.640 --> 23:29.440
because he knows the truth.

23:30.640 --> 23:33.800
You don't get it, do you?

23:33.840 --> 23:37.040
I killed your friend,

23:37.080 --> 23:39.600
Judith Gray, huh?

23:39.640 --> 23:42.400
Not the g-general.

23:42.440 --> 23:43.400
Me.

23:43.440 --> 23:45.720
He has no idea.

23:45.760 --> 23:48.920
Bitch never saw me coming.

23:48.960 --> 23:53.400
So, who is
in c-c-c-c-control now?

23:53.440 --> 23:54.880
Huh?

23:54.920 --> 23:57.520
Who is gonna get paid now?

23:57.560 --> 24:00.960
I don't know--
I don't know Judith Gray.

24:01.000 --> 24:03.040
I never met her.
Who did-- who--

24:03.080 --> 24:05.280
who did the general
tell you I am?

24:15.360 --> 24:17.560
Hey.
Hey.

24:17.600 --> 24:19.760
Listen to me. You...

24:19.800 --> 24:22.120
you don't have to do this.

24:24.840 --> 24:27.520
[grunts, pants]

24:27.560 --> 24:29.720
Please, I-I can-- I can just--

24:29.760 --> 24:32.120
I can-- I can get on a plane.

24:32.160 --> 24:34.160
I can just go home.

24:38.880 --> 24:42.080
I can do this
so you won't feel a thing.

24:42.120 --> 24:43.320
[scoffs]

24:43.360 --> 24:46.840
I can p-p-promise you that.

24:49.120 --> 24:51.080
I-I understand.

24:51.120 --> 24:53.240
[mutters]

24:53.280 --> 24:55.680
I understand.

25:00.240 --> 25:02.240
[exhales]

25:03.320 --> 25:04.840
[gasps]

25:04.880 --> 25:05.840
[panting]:
I'm s--

25:05.880 --> 25:08.880
Sorry. I'm sorry.

25:08.920 --> 25:10.760
I'm sorry.

25:10.800 --> 25:12.760
Here.

25:12.800 --> 25:15.120
I will guide you.

25:15.160 --> 25:17.120
Yeah.

25:17.160 --> 25:19.280
[whispers]:
Yeah.

25:19.320 --> 25:21.360
Thank you.

25:21.400 --> 25:23.800
[panting]

25:42.280 --> 25:44.680
[insects trilling]

25:48.000 --> 25:50.720
Are you sure this is the place?

26:10.400 --> 26:12.960
[bird calling]

26:13.000 --> 26:15.640
[men laughing, chattering]

26:17.400 --> 26:19.800
[man speaking Swahili]

26:25.280 --> 26:27.560
-Leave me alone!
-[shouting in Swahili]

26:34.520 --> 26:37.200
[men laughing,
chattering in Swahili]

26:41.440 --> 26:42.440
[shouting]

26:43.640 --> 26:47.200
Georgie. Georgie.

26:47.240 --> 26:49.200
No! I just want to talk to him!

26:49.240 --> 26:51.440
-Please!
-Run! Run!

26:51.480 --> 26:53.000
Get Violet and run!

26:53.040 --> 26:54.120
What?

26:54.160 --> 26:56.400
Get Violet!
Make sure she's safe!

26:56.440 --> 26:58.280
-VIOLET: Mummy?
-[sobs]

26:58.320 --> 26:59.640
Oh.

27:01.720 --> 27:03.840
-[exhales]
-Mummy?

27:03.880 --> 27:06.840
[gasps]

27:06.880 --> 27:09.480
-[exhales]
-[Adidja panting]

27:11.280 --> 27:13.480
[sighs]

27:13.520 --> 27:15.920
[panting continues]

27:18.920 --> 27:21.440
Shh.

27:21.480 --> 27:24.920
Shh, shh.

27:24.960 --> 27:28.560
-[panting stops]
-[exhales]

27:30.920 --> 27:32.480
[exhales]

27:32.520 --> 27:34.920
[insects trilling]

27:47.680 --> 27:50.320
Ariel?

27:51.880 --> 27:53.280
The doctor sorted me out.

27:53.320 --> 27:56.000
It was the bloody
malaria tablets after all.

28:11.040 --> 28:14.400
[rewinding]

28:14.440 --> 28:17.720
ARIEL [recorded]:
You don't have to do this.

28:17.760 --> 28:20.880
SIDNEY: I can do this
so you won't feel a thing.

28:20.920 --> 28:24.120
I can p-p-promise you that.

28:24.160 --> 28:25.920
Oh, Ariel.

28:25.960 --> 28:29.160
ARIEL:
I understand.

28:29.200 --> 28:31.600
[birds chirping]

28:40.640 --> 28:42.600
[inhales sharply]

28:42.640 --> 28:44.760
Oh.

28:44.800 --> 28:46.320
Morning.

28:46.360 --> 28:48.200
[inhales]

28:48.240 --> 28:50.280
You sleep well?

28:50.320 --> 28:53.400
-No.
-No.

28:54.640 --> 28:56.640
Right.

29:01.000 --> 29:03.960
It should just be a few more
hours till we get there.

29:04.000 --> 29:06.520
[starts engine]

29:12.600 --> 29:15.000
♪ ♪

29:35.640 --> 29:38.000
[brakes squeak]

29:38.040 --> 29:39.280
[shuts engine off]

29:39.320 --> 29:41.720
♪ ♪

29:51.960 --> 29:54.360
[indistinct chatter in distance]

30:01.240 --> 30:02.680
Excuse me.

30:02.720 --> 30:05.080
Have you seen this man?

30:05.120 --> 30:07.440
-Has he been here?
-No, no, no, no.

30:07.480 --> 30:09.960
-No?
-Haven't seen him.

30:11.960 --> 30:14.640
Have you seen this man?
Has he been here?

30:14.680 --> 30:16.680
[speaks Swahili]

30:21.920 --> 30:23.440
Ndio, ndio, ndio.

30:23.480 --> 30:25.440
-Yes, yes. [speaks Swahili]
-You've seen him?

30:25.480 --> 30:28.320
-[speaking Swahili]
-You've seen this man?

30:28.360 --> 30:30.480
-Yes. [speaking Swahili]
-Stay close.

30:30.520 --> 30:33.480
[man continues speaking Swahili]

30:42.520 --> 30:44.520
[speaks Swahili]

30:46.120 --> 30:47.240
You buy, yes?

30:47.280 --> 30:48.640
GEORGIA:
So you haven't seen him?

30:48.680 --> 30:49.640
[man speaks Swahili]

30:49.680 --> 30:50.800
[sighs]

30:50.840 --> 30:52.680
-Adidja.
-[goats bleating]

30:52.720 --> 30:55.120
What's wrong?

30:56.600 --> 30:59.000
Adidja, what is it?

31:03.000 --> 31:05.000
Adidja!

31:08.600 --> 31:11.200
Adidja.

31:20.320 --> 31:22.720
♪ ♪

31:24.920 --> 31:27.520
-[Adidja speaks Swahili]
-[Hasina responds]

31:27.560 --> 31:29.960
[Adidja speaking Swahili]

31:34.520 --> 31:37.000
[speaking Swahili]

31:37.040 --> 31:39.200
-Adidja, what's going on?
-[speaks Swahili]

31:39.240 --> 31:40.920
-HASINA: Do you know her?
-GEORGIA: Yes, she's with me.

31:40.960 --> 31:42.960
[speaks Swahili, grunts]

31:43.000 --> 31:45.880
[speaking Swahili comfortingly]

31:54.760 --> 31:57.960
[crying]

31:58.000 --> 32:00.560
GEORGIA:
Adidja, what's the matter?

32:00.600 --> 32:03.360
-Hasina Okafor.
I'm with the Red Cross.
-Okay.

32:03.400 --> 32:06.000
-What did you just say to her?
-[crying]

32:06.040 --> 32:08.680
Last year, a militia group
came to this village.

32:08.720 --> 32:11.200
They took some of the children
to replenish their numbers.

32:11.240 --> 32:14.080
Everyone else, they killed.

32:14.120 --> 32:17.280
There wasn't a single survivor.

32:17.320 --> 32:19.800
Oh, God.

32:21.320 --> 32:24.720
This girl came here
looking for her mother.

32:28.480 --> 32:32.720
There's a graveyard
for everyone who died.

32:35.960 --> 32:39.280
Can you show me?

32:41.640 --> 32:44.040
[birds singing]

32:59.400 --> 33:03.560
ADIDJA:
I'm sorry for taking you here.

33:03.600 --> 33:05.640
GEORGIA:
It's okay.

33:05.680 --> 33:07.840
ADIDJA:
You're angry.

33:07.880 --> 33:11.000
I tell you I will find that man

33:11.040 --> 33:12.400
-and...
-I understand.

33:14.080 --> 33:16.040
Listen, if you'd just told me
you wanted to find your family,

33:16.080 --> 33:18.440
I'd have taken you.

33:18.480 --> 33:20.160
I would.

33:22.360 --> 33:24.880
I know it's been a really long
time since you've been able

33:24.920 --> 33:29.520
to trust anybody, but, I promise
you, Adidja, you can trust me.

33:29.560 --> 33:32.240
Promise.

33:41.160 --> 33:43.560
♪ ♪

34:13.000 --> 34:16.200
[crying]

34:17.280 --> 34:18.440
[sniffles]

34:18.480 --> 34:20.920
[crying]

34:26.040 --> 34:28.440
[birds singing]

34:31.640 --> 34:33.360
PIETER:
Sorry about the interruption.

34:33.400 --> 34:35.080
Now, where were we, my friend?

34:35.120 --> 34:37.920
SIDNEY:
If the general f-f-finds out

34:37.960 --> 34:41.360
that I'm in any of this,

34:41.400 --> 34:44.960
it is the end, you hear me?

34:45.000 --> 34:47.160
Time to get paid, Sidney.

34:47.200 --> 34:50.880
Once it's done,
Azikiwe will have no choice.

34:50.920 --> 34:54.640
Gut the bitch and get paid.

35:01.920 --> 35:04.080
Get out.

35:12.560 --> 35:14.880
What are you thinking about?

35:15.880 --> 35:18.040
Oh.

35:18.080 --> 35:20.240
Doesn't matter.

35:20.280 --> 35:24.800
I'd like to make my mind busy
with something else.

35:26.840 --> 35:30.400
I was thinking
about my daughter.

35:30.440 --> 35:32.960
I was thinking...

35:33.000 --> 35:34.600
how it's not so easy

35:34.640 --> 35:37.440
to make the bad things
that happen just disappear.

35:44.800 --> 35:46.800
Thank you.

35:56.040 --> 35:59.760
You have a daughter?

35:59.800 --> 36:01.760
I did.

36:01.800 --> 36:05.240
She died
when she was three months old.

36:05.280 --> 36:07.560
You know, then.

36:09.600 --> 36:12.600
Yeah, I know.

36:16.280 --> 36:19.160
[engine starts]

36:27.960 --> 36:29.920
MARTIN:
Look, I'm telling you,

36:29.960 --> 36:32.680
there's a man admitting
to murder on this tape.

36:37.200 --> 36:40.680
You understand
legally this means very little.

36:40.720 --> 36:43.000
[sputters]
Would you just check him out?

36:43.040 --> 36:44.280
That's all I ask.

36:44.320 --> 36:46.040
-You don't have a name.
-Oh.

36:46.080 --> 36:48.080
Sorry to have bothered you.

36:53.280 --> 36:56.120
I want to see all the e-mails
between them.

36:56.160 --> 36:58.440
All of them.

36:58.480 --> 37:00.320
Thank you, Gabriel.

37:00.360 --> 37:03.200
Really appreciate it.

37:05.880 --> 37:07.840
Bonjour.

37:07.880 --> 37:10.240
I would like to see
everything recorded

37:10.280 --> 37:13.480
-on your security cameras
yesterday.
-Uh, no, sir.

37:13.520 --> 37:16.480
That's not allowed.

37:18.080 --> 37:20.960
I would like to see everything

37:21.000 --> 37:24.560
recorded on your
security cameras yesterday,

37:24.600 --> 37:27.280
and I would like to see it now.

37:28.280 --> 37:30.360
There. That's him.

37:30.400 --> 37:32.560
Show me where he takes him.

37:38.040 --> 37:41.120
Hold it right there.

37:41.160 --> 37:44.040
Can you go any closer?

37:46.040 --> 37:48.280
-Thank you.
-Yes, sir.

37:48.320 --> 37:49.920
Thank you very much.

38:04.080 --> 38:07.400
-What's this?
-Oh. It came for you

38:07.440 --> 38:09.400
while you were in the hospital.

38:39.560 --> 38:42.640
Lord recognize my innocence.

38:42.680 --> 38:44.040
Forgive me.

38:44.080 --> 38:47.160
And do not consider me guilty
of this act.

38:49.960 --> 38:51.280
May this man's blood

38:51.320 --> 38:53.880
be on the one
who commanded his murder.

39:05.080 --> 39:06.080
Amen.

39:19.760 --> 39:21.760
♪ ♪

39:47.200 --> 39:49.160
♪ ♪

40:02.280 --> 40:04.440
Well, I wasn't expecting you
till the morning.

40:04.480 --> 40:07.320
Are you sure
this is the best place to be?

40:07.360 --> 40:09.240
It's the last place
they're going to look right now.

40:09.280 --> 40:11.440
And just in case,
I hired a little security.

40:11.480 --> 40:13.120
GEORGIA:
Yeah, I noticed.

40:13.160 --> 40:15.680
Hi.

40:15.720 --> 40:17.560
-I tried to not wake her up.
-May I?

40:17.600 --> 40:20.080
Thanks.

40:29.800 --> 40:32.760
I wish I slept like that.

40:46.240 --> 40:49.600
Ariel and I went to see
Major General Azikiwe.

40:49.640 --> 40:53.440
He's definitely the man
who planted the bomb.

40:53.480 --> 40:55.720
Okay.

40:55.760 --> 40:58.320
But then I had to go out
and get some medication.

40:58.360 --> 41:01.960
I left Ariel alone.

41:02.000 --> 41:03.920
And when I got back
to the hotel,

41:03.960 --> 41:05.640
he was nowhere to be seen.

41:05.680 --> 41:09.040
One of Azikiwe's men took him.

41:09.080 --> 41:10.760
I went to the police.

41:10.800 --> 41:14.120
Was a total waste of time.

41:14.160 --> 41:17.240
I should never have left him.

41:17.280 --> 41:19.640
But you couldn't have known.

41:19.680 --> 41:22.120
I mean, if anyone could find
him, Martin, it's you.

41:22.160 --> 41:24.320
No. He's gone, Georgia.

41:24.360 --> 41:26.320
He knew too much.

41:26.360 --> 41:29.200
-[sighs]
-Anyway,

41:29.240 --> 41:32.080
the people I sent
Judith's hard drive to

41:32.120 --> 41:34.760
found a load of e-mails

41:34.800 --> 41:37.760
between her and Azikiwe.
She was working with him.

41:37.800 --> 41:42.040
He was using army soldiers
to run his personal coltan mine.

41:42.080 --> 41:46.560
Judith smuggled the material out
to Rwanda in aid vehicles,

41:46.600 --> 41:48.560
knowing they wouldn't be checked
crossing the border.

41:48.600 --> 41:50.200
A-And Will must have found out.

41:50.240 --> 41:52.840
And if he knew about that
operation and the kind of money

41:52.880 --> 41:55.200
-it brings in...
-Right, but why
would they keep him alive?

41:55.240 --> 41:58.040
[chuckles] I don't know.

42:02.040 --> 42:06.000
Martin, I'm really sorry
about Ariel.

42:06.040 --> 42:09.160
I've traced the owner
of the vehicle that took him,

42:09.200 --> 42:11.480
and I want to pay that man

42:11.520 --> 42:12.840
a visit in the morning.

42:12.880 --> 42:14.480
Is that a good idea?

42:14.520 --> 42:16.880
Well, he doesn't know
we're coming,

42:16.920 --> 42:19.440
-so we have the upper hand.
-You hope.

42:19.480 --> 42:21.480
Yes, I hope.

42:27.000 --> 42:28.160
You ready?

42:30.560 --> 42:33.400
[whispering]:
Do you think she'll be okay?

42:33.440 --> 42:35.640
Our man's outside.

42:35.680 --> 42:37.840
And when we're back,
we'll find somewhere safe

42:37.880 --> 42:39.120
for her to be looked after.

42:39.160 --> 42:41.360
Okay?

42:41.400 --> 42:44.280
Yeah, okay.

42:51.040 --> 42:53.040
[door closes]

43:03.840 --> 43:05.840
[indistinct chatter]

43:32.760 --> 43:33.760
Who are you?

43:34.560 --> 43:35.640
Can we speak to Sidney?

43:38.080 --> 43:40.840
-Sidney.
-What?

43:48.640 --> 43:49.760
Leave the room.

43:49.800 --> 43:50.800
Move!

43:56.280 --> 43:59.720
-How did you find me?
-MARTIN: It doesn't matter.

43:59.760 --> 44:00.920
The point is, we did.

44:00.960 --> 44:03.960
And the people who led us
to you so quickly

44:04.000 --> 44:06.000
won't take it kindly
if I or my friend

44:06.040 --> 44:08.040
are harmed in any way.

44:09.200 --> 44:11.880
Get out.

44:11.920 --> 44:13.600
It's my son's birthday.

44:13.640 --> 44:15.600
Does he know that
his father's a murderer?

44:15.640 --> 44:20.320
You killed Judith Gray and,
I suspect, Ariel Helgason.

44:20.360 --> 44:22.200
-So you say.
-Uh-huh.

44:22.240 --> 44:26.360
I have CCTV footage of you
leading Ariel out of the hotel.

44:26.400 --> 44:29.400
And thanks to him,
I have you on tape admitting

44:29.440 --> 44:31.560
that you killed Judith Gray.

44:31.600 --> 44:36.240
Now, we could take that tape
to Major General Azikiwe.

44:36.280 --> 44:40.720
Why do I care what you b-bring
to the general?

44:40.760 --> 44:42.440
Because the general
and Judith Gray

44:42.480 --> 44:44.640
were in business together.

44:44.680 --> 44:47.560
But you admit on that tape
that the general

44:47.600 --> 44:49.120
didn't order Judith's death.

44:49.160 --> 44:53.160
And it's very apparent that you
were working for Pieter Bello.

44:53.200 --> 44:55.880
GEORGIA:
I saw what Bello's men did

44:55.920 --> 44:57.560
to the soldiers at the mine.

44:57.600 --> 45:00.240
You were trying to take over
Azikiwe and Judith's operation.

45:00.280 --> 45:02.360
You and Bello.

45:02.400 --> 45:05.360
I have been Azikiwe's friend
for m-m-many years.

45:05.400 --> 45:10.120
Many loyal years.

45:10.160 --> 45:14.680
All I care about is how
Will Mason is involved in this.

45:14.720 --> 45:18.400
-I just want to find Will.
-Will?

45:18.440 --> 45:21.160
You're looking for Will?

45:22.520 --> 45:24.560
[laughing]

45:24.600 --> 45:28.040
We could have saved
a great deal of time

45:28.080 --> 45:29.960
if you asked me before.

45:30.000 --> 45:31.600
Will is in Rwanda.

45:31.640 --> 45:33.760
-What?
-Ruhengeri.

45:33.800 --> 45:35.000
Where?

45:35.040 --> 45:37.320
The red house
with wh-white pillars,

45:37.360 --> 45:39.520
just round the corner
of the New Market.

45:39.560 --> 45:40.640
I've seen it myself.

45:40.680 --> 45:42.840
And I'm supposed
to just believe you.

45:42.880 --> 45:44.520
-[woman gasps]
-[plates shatter on floor]

45:44.560 --> 45:45.880
Ca va, chérie?

45:45.920 --> 45:48.720
WOMAN:
Tout va bien.

45:48.760 --> 45:52.560
If you're lying,
we will go to the general,

45:52.600 --> 45:55.600
we will tell him that
you killed Judith Gray,

45:55.640 --> 45:58.000
and we will tell him that
you have been colluding

45:58.040 --> 45:59.360
with Pieter Bello.

45:59.400 --> 46:02.560
Speak with him, then.

46:12.920 --> 46:16.040
[speaking French]

46:17.800 --> 46:19.960
What is this?

46:24.040 --> 46:25.600
MAN:
Hello?

46:25.640 --> 46:28.360
[impatiently]:
Hello.

46:28.400 --> 46:29.600
Will?

46:29.640 --> 46:31.480
WILL:
Georgia?

46:31.520 --> 46:33.760
Oh, my God, Georgia.
Is that you?

46:33.800 --> 46:36.120
♪ ♪

46:36.160 --> 46:39.440
Georgia?
